{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":5504,"text":"When I was a kid,"},{"time":7398,"text":"the disaster we worried about most \nwas a nuclear war."},{"time":11819,"text":"That's why we had a barrel like this\ndown in our basement,"},{"time":15085,"text":"filled with cans of food and water."},{"time":18256,"text":"When the nuclear attack came,"},{"time":19901,"text":"we were supposed to go downstairs,\nhunker down, and eat out of that barrel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25877,"text":"Today the greatest risk \nof global catastrophe"},{"time":29597,"text":"doesn't look like this."},{"time":32457,"text":"Instead, it looks like this."},{"time":36438,"text":"If anything kills over 10 million people\nin the next few decades,"},{"time":41929,"text":"it's most likely to be \na highly infectious virus"},{"time":45314,"text":"rather than a war."},{"time":47792,"text":"Not missiles, but microbes."},{"time":51679,"text":"Now, part of the reason for this is that"},{"time":53878,"text":"we've invested a huge amount\nin nuclear deterrents."},{"time":58081,"text":"But we've actually invested very little \nin a system to stop an epidemic."},{"time":64129,"text":"We're not ready for the next epidemic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68023,"text":"Let's look at Ebola."},{"time":69758,"text":"I'm sure all of you read about it \nin the newspaper,"},{"time":73615,"text":"lots of tough challenges."},{"time":75221,"text":"I followed it carefully \nthrough the case analysis tools"},{"time":78876,"text":"we use to track polio eradication."},{"time":83721,"text":"And as you look at what went on,"},{"time":85573,"text":"the problem wasn't that there was a system\nthat didn't work well enough,"},{"time":90081,"text":"the problem was that we \ndidn't have a system at all."},{"time":94589,"text":"In fact, there's some pretty obvious\nkey missing pieces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99028,"text":"We didn't have a group of epidemiologists \nready to go, who would have gone,"},{"time":103940,"text":"seen what the disease was,\nseen how far it had spread."},{"time":107696,"text":"The case reports came in on paper."},{"time":110452,"text":"It was very delayed\nbefore they were put online"},{"time":112808,"text":"and they were extremely inaccurate."},{"time":115492,"text":"We didn't have a medical team ready to go."},{"time":117858,"text":"We didn't have a way of preparing people."},{"time":120453,"text":"Now, Médecins Sans Frontières \ndid a great job orchestrating volunteers."},{"time":125784,"text":"But even so, we were far slower\nthan we should have been"},{"time":128880,"text":"getting the thousands of workers\ninto these countries."},{"time":132022,"text":"And a large epidemic would require us\nto have hundreds of thousands of workers."},{"time":140752,"text":"There was no one there \nto look at treatment approaches."},{"time":145155,"text":"No one to look at the diagnostics."},{"time":146946,"text":"No one to figure out \nwhat tools should be used."},{"time":150243,"text":"As an example, we could have \ntaken the blood of survivors,"},{"time":153723,"text":"processed it, and put that plasma\nback in people to protect them."},{"time":159158,"text":"But that was never tried."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161764,"text":"So there was a lot that was missing."},{"time":163520,"text":"And these things \nare really a global failure."},{"time":168305,"text":"The WHO is funded to monitor epidemics,\nbut not to do these things I talked about."},{"time":175049,"text":"Now, in the movies it's quite different."},{"time":177842,"text":"There's a group of handsome\nepidemiologists ready to go,"},{"time":182674,"text":"they move in, they save the day,\nbut that's just pure Hollywood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190177,"text":"The failure to prepare \ncould allow the next epidemic"},{"time":193887,"text":"to be dramatically \nmore devastating than Ebola"},{"time":198735,"text":"Let's look at the progression \nof Ebola over this year."},{"time":204311,"text":"About 10,000 people died, \n"},{"time":207149,"text":"and nearly all were in the three\nWest African countries."},{"time":211846,"text":"There's three reasons why\nit didn't spread more."},{"time":214433,"text":"The first is that there was a lot \nof heroic work by the health workers."},{"time":218874,"text":"They found the people and they \nprevented more infections."},{"time":222136,"text":"The second is the nature of the virus."},{"time":224621,"text":"Ebola does not spread through the air."},{"time":227697,"text":"And by the time you're contagious,"},{"time":229810,"text":"most people are so sick \nthat they're bedridden."},{"time":234220,"text":"Third, it didn't get\ninto many urban areas."},{"time":238411,"text":"And that was just luck."},{"time":240115,"text":"If it had gotten into a lot \nmore urban areas,"},{"time":242355,"text":"the case numbers \nwould have been much larger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245877,"text":"So next time, we might not be so lucky."},{"time":249466,"text":"You can have a virus where people \nfeel well enough while they're infectious"},{"time":254530,"text":"that they get on a plane\nor they go to a market."},{"time":257842,"text":"The source of the virus could be \na natural epidemic like Ebola,"},{"time":260846,"text":"or it could be bioterrorism."},{"time":262826,"text":"So there are things that would literally\nmake things a thousand times worse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267474,"text":"In fact, let's look at a model\nof a virus spread through the air,"},{"time":273475,"text":"like the Spanish Flu back in 1918."},{"time":277630,"text":"So here's what would happen:"},{"time":279560,"text":"It would spread throughout the world\nvery, very quickly."},{"time":283558,"text":"And you can see over 30 million people\ndied from that epidemic."},{"time":288683,"text":"So this is a serious problem."},{"time":290496,"text":"We should be concerned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292257,"text":"But in fact, we can build\na really good response system."},{"time":296692,"text":"We have the benefits of all the science\nand technology that we talk about here."},{"time":301836,"text":"We've got cell phones"},{"time":302883,"text":"to get information from the public \nand get information out to them."},{"time":306140,"text":"We have satellite maps where we can see\nwhere people are and where they're moving."},{"time":310319,"text":"We have advances in biology"},{"time":312627,"text":"that should dramatically change \nthe turnaround time to look at a pathogen"},{"time":316453,"text":"and be able to make drugs and vaccines\nthat fit for that pathogen."},{"time":321322,"text":"So we can have tools,"},{"time":322888,"text":"but those tools need to be put\ninto an overall global health system."},{"time":327500,"text":"And we need preparedness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329793,"text":"The best lessons, I think, \non how to get prepared"},{"time":332257,"text":"are again, what we do for war."},{"time":334758,"text":"For soldiers, we have full-time,\nwaiting to go."},{"time":339005,"text":"We have reserves that can scale \nus up to large numbers."},{"time":342316,"text":"NATO has a mobile unit \nthat can deploy very rapidly."},{"time":346005,"text":"NATO does a lot of war games \nto check, are people well trained?"},{"time":349455,"text":"Do they understand \nabout fuel and logistics"},{"time":351883,"text":"and the same radio frequencies?"},{"time":354241,"text":"So they are absolutely ready to go."},{"time":356779,"text":"So those are the kinds of things\nwe need to deal with an epidemic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361134,"text":"What are the key pieces?"},{"time":363301,"text":"First, we need strong health systems\nin poor countries."},{"time":368591,"text":"That's where mothers \ncan give birth safely,"},{"time":371778,"text":"kids can get all their vaccines."},{"time":373295,"text":"But, also where we'll see \nthe outbreak very early on."},{"time":378154,"text":"We need a medical reserve corps:"},{"time":379935,"text":"lots of people who've got \nthe training and background"},{"time":382501,"text":"who are ready to go, with the expertise."},{"time":385853,"text":"And then we need to pair those\nmedical people with the military."},{"time":390266,"text":"taking advantage of the military's ability\nto move fast, do logistics"},{"time":394417,"text":"and secure areas."},{"time":396220,"text":"We need to do simulations,"},{"time":399129,"text":"germ games, not war games,\nso that we see where the holes are."},{"time":403927,"text":"The last time a germ game \nwas done in the United States"},{"time":406723,"text":"was back in 2001, \nand it didn't go so well."},{"time":410453,"text":"So far the score is germs: 1, people: 0."},{"time":415490,"text":"Finally, we need lots of advanced R&amp;D\nin areas of vaccines and diagnostics."},{"time":421609,"text":"There are some big breakthroughs, \nlike the Adeno-associated virus,"},{"time":425246,"text":"that could work very, very quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429229,"text":"Now I don't have an exact budget\nfor what this would cost,"},{"time":432599,"text":"but I'm quite sure it's very modest\ncompared to the potential harm."},{"time":437095,"text":"The World Bank estimates that \nif we have a worldwide flu epidemic,"},{"time":441740,"text":"global wealth will go down\nby over three trillion dollars"},{"time":445465,"text":"and we'd have millions\nand millions of deaths."},{"time":449332,"text":"These investments \noffer significant benefits"},{"time":452317,"text":"beyond just being ready for the epidemic."},{"time":454518,"text":"The primary healthcare, the R&amp;D,"},{"time":456982,"text":"those things would reduce \nglobal health equity"},{"time":459812,"text":"and make the world more just \nas well as more safe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463502,"text":"So I think this should absolutely\nbe a priority."},{"time":467514,"text":"There's no need to panic."},{"time":468980,"text":"We don't have to hoard cans of spaghetti\nor go down into the basement."},{"time":473469,"text":"But we need to get going,\nbecause time is not on our side."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477309,"text":"In fact, if there's one positive thing\nthat can come out of the Ebola epidemic,"},{"time":483524,"text":"it's that it can serve as an early \nwarning, a wake-up call, to get ready."},{"time":489330,"text":"If we start now, we can be ready \nfor the next epidemic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494978,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496574,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}